    "Furthermore, LLMs can perpetuate harmful social biases around gender, race, religion, and other social constructs from the text they generate (Schramowski et al. 2022).",
    "As a result, many have suggested ways of overcoming the LLMs' biases with the most crucial one being understanding the bias (Liang et al.",
    "2021; Navigli et al 2023; Schramowski et al. 2022) One other effort in debiasing LLMs is to diversify the texts they are trained on, namely, the language of the texts.",
    "This is important not only for democratizing LLMs (Chen et al. 2023) but to ensure better performance across languages that are not English.",
